    <section id="import-auto-idm437583184">
      <title>Modal verbs would, could, can and may  </title>
      <para id="import-auto-idm370895136">.</para>
      <para id="import-auto-idm393059200">Modal verbs can be used for requests or offers</para>
      <para id="import-auto-idm391443680">.</para>
      <section id="import-auto-idm379377456">
        <title>Requests</title>
        <para id="import-auto-idm180774208">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm210399504">I'd like three bags of sand, please.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm210444496">Can I have three bags of cement, please? </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm209644880">Could I have four tins on paint, please?  </para>
      </section>
      <section id="import-auto-idm206371072">
        <title>Offers</title>
        <para id="import-auto-idm572660880">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm520438368">Would you like any cement?  </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm179903616">Can I help you?  </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm210236816">May I help you? </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm177890976">Would you like anything else? </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm376705168">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm210624320">Q: Would you like building sand or rendering sand?</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm205563984">A: I’d like one bag of building sand.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm392729280">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm1373950656">Note: Building sand is used for laying bricks or blocks and rendering sand is used for plastering/rendering walls. </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm554813920">.</para>
      </section>
      <section id="import-auto-idm1374006320">
