      <section id="import-auto-idm574956384">
        <title>Many and much </title>
        <para id="import-auto-idm1374760864">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm519864144">Many is used for nouns that are countable. Much is used for nouns that are uncountable. </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm392667792">Example:  How many tins of paint would you like?  (tins are countable) </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm547866368">How much paint would you like? (paint is uncountable)</para>
      </section>
      <section id="import-auto-idm397444144">
        <title>Some/any </title>
        <para id="import-auto-idm594511488">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm527510736">Some or any have similar meanings. Some is more common in positive statements. Some and any are common in questions. </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm182216912">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm367353392">Some can be used for general questions and requests. </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm1373729568">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm597079904">I'd like some nails, please.  </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm439555600">Some of the carpenters worked on Saturday. (not all) </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm411054000">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm570501792">Any can be used for open questions.  </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm478560928">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm391952768">Do you have any screws?  </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm398809120">We don't have any screws. (none) </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm437073696">You can use any colour paint. (all) </para>
      </section>
